Blocks.childText: No. 55. SHELLY. S.M. L. SPOHR (1784-1859). 1 Behold the throne of grace; The promise calls us near; There Jesus shows a smiling face, And waits to answer prayer. 2 My soul, ask what thou wilt, Thou canst not be too bold; Since his own blood for thee he spilt, What else can he withhold? 3 Thine image, Lord, bestow, Thy presence and thy love, That we may serve thee here below, And reign with thee above. 4 Teach us to live by faith, Conform our wills to thine; Let us victorious be in death, And then in glory shine. Rev. JOHN NEWTON (1725 - 1807). (58) (1784-1859) Behold the throne of grace
